  The **Pixel 9**, **Pixel 9 Pro**, and **Pixel 9 Pro XL** are a group of [Android](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_(operating_system) "Android (operating system)")-based [smartphones](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smartphone "Smartphone") designed, developed, and marketed by [Google](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google "Google") as part of the [Google Pixel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Pixel "Google Pixel") product line. They serve as the successor to the [Pixel 8](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_8 "Pixel 8") and [Pixel 8 Pro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_8_Pro "Pixel 8 Pro"), respectively. Sporting a redesigned appearance and powered by the fourth-generation [Google Tensor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Tensor "Google Tensor") [system-on-chip](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/System-on-chip "System-on-chip"), the phones are heavily integrated with [Gemini](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gemini_(chatbot) "Gemini (chatbot)")-branded [artificial intelligence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_intelligence "Artificial intelligence") features.
  
  The Pixel 9, Pixel 9 Pro, and Pixel 9 Pro XL were officially announced on August 13, 2024, at the annual [Made by Google](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Made_by_Google "Made by Google") event, and were released in the United States on August 22 and September 4 for the Pixel 9 Pro Fold.
  
  ## History
  
  \[ [edit](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pixel_9&action=edit&section=1 "Edit section: History")\]
  
  [![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Pixel_9_%26_Pixel_9_Pro_Hands-On_Impressions_%28ShoAndTech%29_%282160p_24fps_VP9_LQ-160kbit_Opus%29-00.02.08.000.png/250px-Pixel_9_%26_Pixel_9_Pro_Hands-On_Impressions_%28ShoAndTech%29_%282160p_24fps_VP9_LQ-160kbit_Opus%29-00.02.08.000.png)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pixel_9_%26_Pixel_9_Pro_Hands-On_Impressions_(ShoAndTech)_(2160p_24fps_VP9_LQ-160kbit_Opus)-00.02.08.000.png) The Pixel 9 (R) and 9 Pro XL (L), both in "Porcelain" color
  
  The Pixel 9 series was approved by the [Federal Communications Commission](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Communications_Commission "Federal Communications Commission") (FCC) in July 2024.[\[3\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-FCC-3) After previewing the Pro model the same month,[\[4\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TeaserAP-4)[\[5\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TeaserVerge-5) Google officially announced the Pixel 9, Pixel 9 Pro, and Pixel 9 Pro XL on August 13, alongside the [Pixel 9 Pro Fold](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9_Pro_Fold "Pixel 9 Pro Fold") and [Pixel Watch 3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_Watch_3 "Pixel Watch 3"), at the annual [Made by Google](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Made_by_Google "Made by Google") event.[\[6\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-WiredLaunch-6) Numerous observers noted the unusually early timing of the launch event, which was traditionally held in September after [Apple](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Inc. "Apple Inc.")'s annual launch of the new [iPhone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPhone "IPhone"). Commentators described this as an attempt to “outshine” Apple, its longtime rival, and demonstrate its [artificial intelligence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_intelligence "Artificial intelligence") (AI) prowess.[\[a\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-13) Several also took note of Google's usually frequent veiled attacks targeting Apple.[\[13\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-Dinged-14)[\[11\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AIRace-11) All three phones became available for pre-order the same day; the Pixel 9 and Pixel 9 Pro XL were made available on August 22 while the Pro was available on September 4, the latter alongside the Pixel 9 Pro Fold, in 32 countries.[\[14\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-NYTLaunch-15)[\[15\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-Countries-16)
  
  Pixel 9 owners on Verizon US can text from anywhere outside the network reach via satellite.[\[16\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-17)
  
  ## Specifications
  
  \[ [edit](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pixel_9&action=edit&section=2 "Edit section: Specifications")\]
  
  ### Design
  
  \[ [edit](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pixel_9&action=edit&section=3 "Edit section: Design")\]
  
  The Pixel 9, Pixel 9 Pro, and Pixel 9 Pro XL feature a redesigned appearance while retaining the overall [design language](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design_language "Design language") that began with the [Pixel 6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_6 "Pixel 6") series, with the edges now flat rather than curved and the camera bar taking the shape of "an elongated, free-floating \[…\] oval".[\[17\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-ProShow-18)[\[18\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-LoveHate-19) They are each available in four colors:[\[6\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-WiredLaunch-6)
  
  | Pixel 9 |  | Pixel 9 Pro and 9 Pro XL |
