  ### Hardware
  
  \[ [edit](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pixel_9&action=edit&section=4 "Edit section: Hardware")\]
  
  In a departure from previous generations, the Pixel 9 series was offered in three models: the base model, a “Pro” model, and a new “Pro XL” model. The Pixel 9 and Pixel 9 Pro are near-identical in size, with a 6.3 in (160 mm) screen size, while the Pixel 9 Pro XL is slightly larger at 6.7 in (171 mm).[\[17\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-ProShow-18)[\[19\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TotalEvolution-20) A key distinction between the base and Pro models lies in the camera setup, with the higher-end models sporting a 48- [megapixel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Megapixel "Megapixel") [telephoto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telephoto "Telephoto") rear camera in addition to the standard 50- and 48-megapixel [wide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wide-angle_lens "Wide-angle lens") and [ultrawide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultra_wide_angle_lens "Ultra wide angle lens") lenses; the Pro models also include a 42-megapixel ultrawide front camera compared to 10.5 megapixels on the base.[\[6\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-WiredLaunch-6)
  
  All three phones are powered by the fourth-generation [Google Tensor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Tensor "Google Tensor") [system-on-chip](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/System-on-chip "System-on-chip") (SoC), marketed as "Google Tensor G4", and the [Titan M2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Titan_M "Titan M") security [co-processor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Co-processor "Co-processor").[\[20\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-EngadgetLaunch-21)[\[21\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TCLaunch-22) The upgraded [Samsung Exynos](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samsung_Exynos "Samsung Exynos") 5400 modem on the new Tensor chip enhances the Pixel 9's satellite connectivity, enabling the ability to [contact emergency services via satellite](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satellite_emergency_notification_device "Satellite emergency notification device"), similar to the feature introduced by Apple on the [iPhone 14](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPhone_14 "IPhone 14") and the first [Android](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_(operating_system) "Android (operating system)") phone to be equipped with this technology. Dubbed “Satellite SOS”, Google partnered with [satellite network](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satellite_network "Satellite network") provider [Skylo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skylo "Skylo") and SOS dispatch center [Garmin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garmin "Garmin") on the feature, which was made available for free for two years.[\[22\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-Satellite9to5-23)[\[23\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-SatelliteWired-24)[\[24\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-SatelliteZDNET-25) Tensor G4 is also the first SoC to run [Gemini Nano](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gemini_Nano "Gemini Nano"), a version of the [Gemini](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gemini_(language_model) "Gemini (language model)") [large language model](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Large_language_model "Large language model") (LLM), with [multimodality](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multimodality "Multimodality").[\[25\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-GeminiNano-26)
  
  ### Software
  
  \[ [edit](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pixel_9&action=edit&section=5 "Edit section: Software")\]
  
  As with prior Pixel generations, the Pixel 9 series is equipped with numerous AI-powered features, with the [Associated Press](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Associated_Press "Associated Press") calling it a "vessel for the AI technology that is expected to reshape the way people live and work".[\[11\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AIRace-11) Google dedicated the first half-hour of its launch event discussing its advances in the field before unveiling its new devices.[\[26\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-Overshadowed-27) [Gemini](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gemini_(chatbot) "Gemini (chatbot)"), a generative AI–powered [chatbot](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chatbot "Chatbot") launched in 2023 in response to [OpenAI](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenAI "OpenAI")'s [ChatGPT](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ChatGPT "ChatGPT"), was frequently spotlighted, replacing the [Google Assistant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Assistant "Google Assistant") as the new default [virtual assistant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_assistant "Virtual assistant") on Pixel and heavily integrating into the Pixel 9 series.[\[27\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TrainWreck-28)[\[28\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AIPowered-29) In order to facilitate on-device AI processing, the [RAM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RAM "RAM") on the Pixel 9 series was substantially increased.[\[28\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AIPowered-29)[\[20\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-EngadgetLaunch-21) Google also debuted Gemini Live, a new voice chat mode powered by the [Imagen 3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imagen_(text-to-image_model) "Imagen (text-to-image model)") [text-to-image model](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Text-to-image_model "Text-to-image model").[\[29\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-GeminiLiveVerge-30)[\[30\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-GeminiLiveWSJ-31)
  
  Other AI-powered features included Pixel Studio, an [image generation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_intelligence_art "Artificial intelligence art") app; Pixel Screenshots, a screenshot management and analysis app; Add Me, the ability to retroactively add subjects to photos; Pixel Weather, a new [weather forecast](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weather_forecast "Weather forecast") app; Call Notes, which summarizes phone calls while running on-device; and miscellaneous camera updates.[\[31\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AIFeaturesTC-32)[\[32\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AIFeaturesVerge-33)[\[33\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AIFeaturesWired-34) Breaking with tradition, the Pixel 9 series was shipped with the year-old [Android 14](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_14 "Android 14") rather than [Android 15](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_15 "Android 15"), likely due to the earlier-than-usual timeframe;[\[34\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-Android15Engadget-35)[\[35\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-Android159to5-36) the phones were updated with Android 15 via a “Pixel Drop” software update, formerly known as Feature Drops, on October 15.[\[36\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-Android15Verge-37) Continuing the [Pixel 8](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_8 "Pixel 8")'s trend, the phones will receive seven years of major OS upgrades, with support extending to 2031.[\[6\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-WiredLaunch-6)[\[21\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TCLaunch-22)
  
  ## Marketing
  
  \[ [edit](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pixel_9&action=edit&section=6 "Edit section: Marketing")\]
  
  An “after party” livestream hosted by actress [Keke Palmer](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keke_Palmer "Keke Palmer") and featuring celebrity guest appearances followed the Made by Google event.[\[37\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AfterParty-38) Days after the phones' launch, Google generated controversy after several [social media influencers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_media_influencers "Social media influencers") part of the seven-year-old #TeamPixel marketing program posted screenshots of a new clause stipulating that participants must not show preference for competitors when creating content with the Pixel 9. Missing context led to confusion online regarding the extent of the restriction, which only applied to #TeamPixel influencers. Google later apologized and removed the clause from the agreement.[\[38\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TeamPixelVerge-39)[\[39\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TeamPixelMashable-40)[\[40\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TeamPixelInc-41)
  
  In February 2025, Google released a commercial titled “Dream Job” which advertised Gemini on the Pixel 9, ahead of its airing during [Super Bowl LIX](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_Bowl_LIX "Super Bowl LIX"). One of Google's two [Super Bowl spots](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_Bowl_commercials "Super Bowl commercials") that year, the 60-second commercial featured a father using Gemini on his Pixel 9 to prepare for a job interview. Google also ran a third commercial entitled “Party Blitz” online, in which a man "attempts to impress his girlfriend's family by using Gemini \[on his Pixel 9\] to become a football expert".[\[41\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-DreamJobTHR-42)[\[42\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-DreamJobAW-43)[\[43\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-DreamJobAdAge-44)
  
  ## Reception
  
  \[ [edit](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pixel_9&action=edit&section=7 "Edit section: Reception")\]
  
  In his initial reaction to the Pixel 9 series, _Android Police_'s Rajesh Pandey praised the overall design but disliked the iPhone-esque flat edges and polished metal frame.[\[18\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-LoveHate-19) His colleague Taylor Kerns questioned the absence of an “XL” version of the base model,[\[44\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-XLHole-45) while Rebecca Isaacs of _[Forbes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forbes "Forbes")_ welcomed the addition of small-sized Pro model and the enhanced build quality.[\[45\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-ForbesHandsOn-46) Pandey and Kerns' colleague Will Sattelberg concurred but had mixed reactions to the AI-powered features.[\[46\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-AndroidPoliceHandsOn-47) Allison Johnson of _[The Verge](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Verge "The Verge")_ was impressed by the camera features, writing in a headline, "The Pixel 9 Pro XL showed me the future of AI photography".[\[47\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-VergeHandsOn-48) Writing for _[Mashable](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mashable "Mashable")_, Kimberly Gedeon was drawn to the design of the 9 Pro XL, praising the upgraded Super Res Zoom feature and AI-powered features.[\[48\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-MashableHandsOn-49) _[PCMag](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PCMag "PCMag")_'s Iyaz Akhtar called the rear design of the phones “divisive” but “sleek”.[\[49\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-PCMagHandsOn-50) Kyle Barr of _[Gizmodo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gizmodo "Gizmodo")_ and Philip Michaels of _[Tom's Guide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom%27s_Guide "Tom's Guide")_ both found themselves particularly attracted to the Pixel Screenshots app.[\[50\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-GizmodoHandsOn-51)[\[51\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-TomsGuideHandsOn-52) Kerry Wan of _[ZDNET](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ZDNET "ZDNET")_ predicted that the phones would be a " [sleeper hit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sleeper_hit "Sleeper hit")".[\[52\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-ZDNETHandsOn-53)
  
  The Pixel 9's Tensor G4 processor has also received mixed reviews. While it was praised for improved AI capabilities, some have criticized its poor efficiency under heavy load and lack of performance improvements over the Tensor G3, especially when compared to other flagship processors at the time.[\[53\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-54)[\[54\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-55)[\[55\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-56) Soniya Jobanputra, a lead member of the Pixel's product management team, told [_The Financial Express_](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Financial_Express_(India) "The Financial Express (India)") that the G4 was not designed to "beat some specific benchmark that’s out there. We’re designing it to meet our use cases”.[\[56\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-57)
  
  [GrapheneOS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GrapheneOS "GrapheneOS") began officially supporting the Pixel 9, Pixel 9 Pro, and Pixel 9 Pro XL in August 2024, with full compatibility, shortly after the devices began shipping to consumers.[\[57\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-58)[\[58\]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixel_9#cite_note-59)
  
